result.adr_address: 117 First St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 117 First St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Andrea's Bagel Crust Pizza

reviews.text: The pizza was good but the crust was definitely nothing close to a bagel. This was disappointing as I went far out of my way to try this place. The crust is very much normal bread crust, not even with a cooked thin layer of oil at the bottom for that extra crisp factor.  Staff is very nice, they have wifi and will let you charge your devices there.

The moment of truth when I opened the soup that weighs almost nothing. This half tub of microwave-reheated vegetable pasta soup costed me 70 honkies. 

To be fair, it wasn't just microwave reheated, it was then simmered on a pan. But the point is, 70 bloody honkies of this half cup of soup. I understand it's hipstery Sai Ying Poon, but how could this watery reheated soup with soggy pasta bits and mushy vegetable lumps ask for 70 bucks? And I had to wait for nearly 15 min for this. Seriously. Negative 5 stars.
Must try pizza in Sai Ying Pun area

Owner is not friendly. The crust is not a bagel crust. I've ordered the same pizza (urban hangover cure) twice and they were both different. One time the flavor was really good. The other time they put some kind of spicy mayo or sriracha mayo on top of the pizza which made it worse. The place itself is clean and fast though.
Pepperoni pizza was tasty, hot and fresh made to order
